Structs/Device.html#/s:7sapataz6DeviceV5.name: model
Structs/Device.html#/s:7sapataz6DeviceV5.abstract: Model is the Device Model and can have values such as iPhone, iPad or Apple TV.

Structs/Device.html#/s:7sapataz6DeviceV1.name: operatingSystem
Structs/Device.html#/s:7sapataz6DeviceV1.abstract: Operating System is the Device OS and can have values such as iOS or tvOS.

Structs/Device.html#/s:7sapataz6DeviceV7.name: version
Structs/Device.html#/s:7sapataz6DeviceV7.abstract: Version is the Device OS version and can have values such as 10.1.

Structs/Device.html#/s:7sapataz6DeviceV9.name: osVersion
Structs/Device.html#/s:7sapataz6DeviceV9.abstract: OS Version is the concatenation of operatingSystem with version. Can be something as iPad 10.3

Structs/Device.html.name: Device
Structs/Device.html.abstract: Device is a struct that groups all the data about the device. It is a convenience struct.

Classes/Identifier.html.name: Identifier
Classes/Identifier.html.abstract: Identifier is just a wrapper for the UUID class.
